Pop a #pot{} of water onto high heat and bring to the boil. When boiling, pour in the
@brown basmati rice{350%g}, @cinnamon stick{1} and a generous pinch of @salt{pinch}.
Cook for ~{25%minutes} and then drain. Return the rice to the pot and keep warm
by covering the pot with a #lid{}.

Pre-heat your #grill{} to medium. While your rice cooks, prepare the vegetables.
Remove the core from the @red pepper{2} and chop into 1cm thick slices. Peel and
grate the @garlic clove{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{5}.

Mix the @pork medallion{4} with the @tamarind sauce{2%tbsp} and the @sugar{1%tsp}.
Mix well and then add a third of the @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp}.

Grill the pork on a #baking tray{} lined with foil for ~{16%minutes}. Turn after
~{8%minutes}.

> The pork are cooked when the centre is no longer pink.

As your pork cooks, heat a #frying pan{} or #wok{} over high heat. Add a splash
of @olive oil{1%splash} and when the oil is hot, cook the red peppers for
~{10%minutes}, stirring frequently. After ~{10%minutes}, add the garlic and the
remaining soy sauce. Cook for ~{1%minute} longer and then remove the pan from the
heat. Mix in the chopped coriander.

Pop your cooked pork into a #bowl{} with any of the cooked marinade and juices
from the foil. Let them rest for ~{1%minute} or so. Cut each piece of pork into
five slices when you are ready to serve and reserve any of the cooked marinade
and juices. Mix the @honey{1%tbsp} into the cooking juices from your pork.

To serve, spoon a generous amount of your rice onto the centre of your #plate{}.
Top with some red peppers and then with your sliced pork. Drizzle your tamarind
and honey juices on top and enjoy!